body:
A lot of people always do this, always judging the interaction videos, which always shows one side of the character, like Rakan who everyone thought he just screams everything but when reading and listening to his actual lines, he does have feelings to his kind and Xayah. 

When I first listened to Aatrox by his interactions, I did thought he just shouts a lot because he does love blood and carnage. But when I looked up his other voice lines, it showed a new light on Aatrox. Though it isn&#039;t the same as the old Aatrox, he becomes an actual character with depth to it other than shout and kill everyone.

Some quotes [(from the league wiki)](http://leagueoflegends.wikia.com/wiki/Aatrox#PBE) that I found most interesting

&quot;I touched the stars... And saw the glorious light of a thousand suns... Now, blinded by this elegence, how could my purpose be anything... but dark...&quot;

&quot;I am but an unholy copy of life... A mockery of its freedom... And born in the cruel betrayal of the noble ideals I would&#039;ve served.&quot;

&quot;We had another name once... Now, we are Darkin.&quot;

 &quot;I march to death... Though I wish it was my own...&quot;

&quot;This cursed form... This crude decaying flesh! I loathe it!&quot;

&quot;Am I the abyss? Or did I gaze into it?&quot;

&quot;To war Aatrox! They shall not rob us of our nobility! We shall stand, and spit venom at our tormentors for eternity!&quot;


So next time when a champion like {{champion:9}} {{champion:82}} or {{champion:72}}  gets updated, don&#039;t judge the interaction video that skinspotlights do. Listen and/or read each line, and analyse those voice lines instead, they reveal more than what the interactions videos do.

replies.body:
Looking at his voice lines on the Wiki, this Aatrox is actually a lot more somber than I originally believed;
"I am but an unholy copy of life... A mockery of its freedom... And born in the cruel betrayal of the noble ideals I would've served."
"How far I have fallen! A god... reduced to a prisoner!"

But most intresting to me is this line;
"We march to battle... Let me carve flesh, let me cloak myself in the slaughter. Hide me in their carnage... Hide me from this suffering..."
What this tells me is that Aatrox dosn't kill because he enjoys it (as Rhaast does), he kills to scare away the suffering. The suffering of knowing the monster he's become. 
{{sticker:zombie-nunu-tears}}
